Program: Omnibus
Title: The Savoy at 100
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jnj
Last Broadcast Date: 02 August 1989
A look at the history of the hotel on the Strand in London which was built by Richard D'Oyly Carte with proceeds from the success of his opera 'The Mikado'. It was the first hotel in London with running water, electricity and lifts